    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vases intended to contain offerings or to themselves serve as an offering in a religious or funerary context. Examples exist from ancient times and in many cultures, including the following: ancient Egypt, Greece, and Rome; Asian cultures; the Pre-Columbian Americas; and in modern western culture.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
